metadata.name: De/FragV2 #339
metadata.description:
The second piece in this series is dedicated to another fundamental algorithm in computer graphics: Voronoi. It's origin precedes its use with computers by several decades, or centuries, depending on who to credit, since science always is a continuum. In the generative art & design field, the algorithm has been an instrumental tool for generation(s) of practioners, sadly often to the point of turning cliché.

In this piece I've attempted to "break" the classic resulting aesthetics of this algorithm and focus more on revealing its inner workings. There are many ways of computing a Voronoi diagram. The so called Jump Flood Algorithm (JFA) proved to be the visually most interesting approach to me. Again, as with the previous De/Frag piece, here the algorithm has been slowed down, timesliced and customized in dozens of ways to result in a more painterly character overall and produce a variety of new shapes & textures.

Fullscreen compatible (Press 'S' to toggle square frame). Made with love & thi.ng/umbrella

metadata.name: Fractures #74
metadata.description:
Fractures is a personal interpretation of how beauty can emerge from broken shapes.

Starting from a simple and regular geometric shape, Fractures succeeds in breaking the initial visual monotony thanks to a recursive division system applied to the triangles of the initial polygon. Line patterns, random color inversions, grainy and charcoal effect are then added to give the final image a nice organic feel.

Press [P] to generate and save a 4000x4000 .png file. This can take some time, be patient.

Artist: Estienne
Dec 2021

metadata.description:

metadata.name: Paper Mandala #297
metadata.description:
A collaboration with P1xelboy and Paper Buddha.
Beautiful paper mandalas made purely with code in Paper Buddha's style.
Features include:
27 different palettes
3 different mandala types (Lotus, Starburst Style 1 and Starburst Style 2)
Four sections of the mandala with one of 10 different pattern types (Dots, Checks, Crosses, Triangles, Stripes, Circles, Polygons, Lazers, Quadrants and Hatching)
4 different direction types of shadow - of varying length
Randomly placed star background
Randomly placed Nebula
Possible Special Pattern Effect with darker stippling pattern
Possible Nirvana Effect where random colors are added to one of either Golden, Silver, Bronze, Blue Moon or Sea Green palettes.

Using only code, this produces a unique output which does take a few seconds to load.
Press "S" to Save your unique Paper Mandala as a 2048 x 2048 JPG
Press "R" for a random shuffle effect - (please wait for reload) - Refresh page to reset

The project works in a responsive browser, so to set up for phone background or watch, resize the browser accordingly and Alt + Print Screen to get an appropriately sized image.

Offered as a Dutch Auction, holders of the first 20 tokens (1-20) will receive additional benefits in the form of utility for future releases in the P1xelboy/Paper Mandala collaboration series. (exact details to be determined)
This utility will remain attached to tokens 1-20 and transfer to the new owner upon subsequent secondary sales.

Uses p5.js and p5.pattern
@p1x3lboy @paperbuddha - September 2022

metadata.name: Fragment #125
metadata.description:
▪️ 28 Variables
▪️ [left mouse button] hold to rotate
▪️ [mouse wheel] to zoom in and out
▪️ [right mouse button] to reset the view
▪️ [r] to toggle auto rotation [on by default]
▪️ [i] to toggle inverted colours
▪️ [s] to open the image capture popup on the top right [Live only capture]
▪️▪️ Maximum recommended width and height is 4096px [Higher resolutions might fail]
▪️ The piece does not stretch but instead it adjusts to the screen size and ratio
▪️ Designed to have a strong visual impact so might not be suitable for mobile
▪️ Created as a free gift to holders of any of my projects on fxhash as of 03.08.2022

metadata.name: A Less Traveled Path #158
metadata.description:
"I shall be telling this with a sigh
Somewhere ages and ages hence:
Two roads diverged in a wood, and I—
I took the one less traveled by,
And that has made all the difference."

- Robert Frost, The Road Not Taken



=========

Controls:
[1] set resolution to 1024x1024 (default)
[2] set resolution to 2048x2048 
[3] set resolution to 4096x4096
[0] set resolution to window size (might help on lower end computers)

[c] capture a screenshot at rendered resolution


Made with cables.gl, a node-based webgl environment
XALTED 2022
